.NET Framework 3.5.name: VRTK_InteractTouch
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: The Interact Touch script is usually applied to a Controller and provides a collider to know when the controller is touching something.
.NET Framework 3.5.remarks:
Colliders are created for the controller and by default the selected controller SDK will have a set of colliders for the given default controller of that SDK.

 A custom collider can be provided by the Custom Rigidbody Object parameter.
.NET Framework 3.5.example: VRTK/Examples/005_Controller/BasicObjectGrabbing demonstrates the highlighting of objects that have the VRTK_InteractableObject script added to them to show the ability to highlight interactable objects when they are touched by the controllers.

ForceStopTouching()
methods.summary: The ForceStopTouching method will stop the controller from touching an object even if the controller is physically touching the object still.

methods.name: ForceTouch(GameObject obj)
methods.summary: The ForceTouch method will attempt to force the controller to touch the given game object. This is useful if an object that isn't being touched is required to be grabbed or used as the controller doesn't physically have to be touching it to be forced to interact with it.

params.value: The game object to attempt to force touch.

methods.name: GetTouchedObject()
methods.summary: The GetTouchedObject method returns the current object being touched by the controller.
methods.returns: The game object of what is currently being touched by this controller.

methods.name: IsObjectInteractable(GameObject obj)
methods.summary: The IsObjectInteractable method is used to check if a given game object is of type VRTK_InteractableObject and whether the object is enabled.
methods.returns: Is true if the given object is of type VRTK_InteractableObject.

params.value: The game object to check to see if it's interactable.

methods.name: IsRigidBodyActive()
methods.summary: The IsRigidBodyActive method checks to see if the rigidbody on the controller object is active and can affect other rigidbodies in the scene.
methods.returns: Is true if the rigidbody on the controller is currently active and able to affect other scene rigidbodies.

methods.name: IsRigidBodyForcedActive()
methods.summary: The IsRigidBodyForcedActive method checks to see if the rigidbody on the controller object has been forced into the active state.
methods.returns: Is true if the rigidbody is active and has been forced into the active state.

ToggleControllerRigidBody(bool state, bool forceToggle)
methods.summary: The ToggleControllerRigidBody method toggles the controller's rigidbody's ability to detect collisions. If it is true then the controller rigidbody will collide with other collidable game objects.

params.value: The state of whether the rigidbody is on or off. true toggles the rigidbody on and false turns it off.
Determines if the rigidbody has been forced into it's new state by another script. This can be used to override other non-force settings. Defaults to false
